'''William Alexander "Bill" McLaren''' {{post-nominals|country=AUS|CBE}} (8 May 1898{{spaced endash}}30 September 1973) was a senior Australian public servant. He was [[Departmental secretary|Secretary]] of the [[Department of the Interior (1939–1972)|Department of the Interior]] between 1949 and 1963.

==Life and career==
Bill McLaren was born in Sydney on 8 May 1898.<ref name=Carnell>{{citation|url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/mclaren-william-alexander-11002|deadurl=no|work=Australian Dictionary of Biography|publisher=Australian National University|archivedate=25 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425064020/http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/mclaren-william-alexander-11002|title=
McLaren, William Alexander (1898–1973)|first=Ian|last=Carnell}}</ref>

McLaren moved to [[Canberra]] in 1945 into the [[Australian Public Service]] as the Commonwealth Director of War Service Land Settlement.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article110750116|title=Obituary: Mr W. A. McLaren|date=1 October 1973|newspaper=The Canberra Times|page=6}}</ref>

Between 1949 and 1963, McLaren was Secretary of the Department of the Interior.<ref name="NAA CA 31">{{citation|title=CA 31: Department of the Interior [II], Central Office|url=http://naa12.naa.gov.au/scripts/SearchOld.asp?Number=CA+31|publisher=National Archives of Australia|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

McLaren died on 30 September 1970.<ref name=Carnell/>

==Awards==
McLaren was made a Commander of the Order of the British Empire in 1954.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=1065018&search_type=quick&showInd=true|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425064152/http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=1065018&search_type=quick&showInd=true|archivedate=25 April 2014|title=Search Australian Honours: McLAREN, William Alexander|publisher=Australian Government|work=itsanhonour.gov.au}}</ref>

